benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Retrieve bundle custom fields

covered: Valid Request: The tests validate successful GET for existing bundles with default and explicit audit levels (TC01-TC03) and edge cases with max/min fields (TC11-TC12).
Empty Response: TC04 confirms 200 with an empty array when no custom fields exist.
Query Parameters: Tests cover multiple audit values (NONE default, FULL, MINIMAL) and invalid values (TC07, TC13), plus extra parameters that are ignored (TC10).
Authorization: TC08 covers 401 unauthorized when token is missing or invalid.
Error Handling and Status Codes: Tests cover 404 not found (TC05), 400 for invalid bundleId (TC06) and invalid audit parameters (TC07, TC13), and 503 service unavailability (TC09, TC16).
Security: Tests include SQL injection (TC17) and XSS (TC18) attempts.
Performance and Concurrency: TC14 screen tests for long running operations; TC19 tests concurrent requests for multiple bundleIds.
Structure and Accessibility: TC20 validates Content-Type is application/json and body is a JSON array of CustomField objects.
Regression and Integration: TC15 validates regression fix; TC16 tests integration when audit service is unavailable.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large result sets.
Rate Limiting: No tests covering rate limiting or throttling under burst load.
Caching Behavior: No tests checking caching headers such as ETag or Cache-Control.
Authorization Edge Case: No test for 403 Forbidden when token has insufficient permissions.
Internal server error: No explicit test for 500 Internal Server Error.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination (page and size) to validate large result sets and proper pagination behavior.
Add a 403 Forbidden test to verify behavior when authenticated users lack permissions.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers and cache invalidation semantics.
Add rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure proper handling under high load.
Add explicit 500 Internal Server Error test to validate server side error handling.
